summary: Pull Days: Scheduling Vertical vs Horizontal Pulls via /r/Fitness
title: Pull Days: Scheduling Vertical vs Horizontal Pulls via /r/Fitness
body:
As the tiltle suggests, I’ve been wondering what is the best way to program your pull days in a PPL split. I usually do pullups as my main pull movement on day A and barbell rows on day B. For my 2nd exercise I then switch to a horizontal pull in day A and a vertical on day B. And then, on the 3rd exercise, I go back to a vertical pull on day A and a horizontal pull on day B. To be easier to understand:

DAY A: Pullups 4x6, Horizontal Pull 4x8, Vertical Pull 4x12

DAY B: Barbell Row 4x6, Vertical Pull 4x8, Horizontal Pull 4x12

Now, I don’t know how much this is relevant or how much does it affect your muscle/strength, but I’m just curious about how you guys plan your pull days. Do you do all of your vertical pulls in one day and the horizontal pulls in another? Do you have a different vertical to horizontal ratio scheme? Do you do them in a different order? Etc…



Submitted October 22, 2018 at 04:19AM by thesosomark
via reddit https://ift.tt/2CZ9qI3
